AB  - Eighteen normally calved Mehsana buffaloes studied for postpartum oestrus (non-fertile and fertile oestrus) revealed higher levels of serum total cholesterol (P < 0.05) and serum inorganic phosphorus, alkaline phosphatase and acetylcholinesterase enzymes during fertile oestrus as compared to non-fertile oestrus. However, a reverse trend was observed for serum. calcium. The findings revealed that total cholesterol levels were more useful than other estimates.
