AB  - Studies of Ca partition in the blood serum of 50 infants, ranging from 5 to 22 days in age, are reported, together with determinations of the serum inorganic phosphates, chlorides and protein fractions and the whole blood cholesterol. The total serum Ca, as determined in 32 cases, averaged 11.4 mgm. per 100 ccm. of serum. The average diffusible serum Ca, as estimated in 42 determinations, was 5.3 mgm. or 46.7%. The nondiffusible Ca averaged 6.2 mgm., or 53.6%, in 31 determinations. No significant statistical correlation could be found between the total or diffusible Ca and the inorganic phosphates, protein fractions, chlorides or cholesterol.
