LA  - English
CP  - 9th World Congress on the Menopause
AB  - The purpose of this study was to evaluate characteristics of perimenopausal women in Korea. We divided 233 perimenopausal women into 4 groups by age. We asked them for their climacteric symptoms and measured bone mineral densities, biochemical markers of bone turnover, lipid profiles, total serum calcium and uric acid. The common symptoms of Korean menopausal women were backache, arthralgia, hot flashes and urinary frequency in order of frequency. The bone mineral densities of climacteric women significantly decreased by increasing age. The serum alkaline phosphatase among biochemical markers significantly increased by increasing age. The levers of HDL-cholesterol decreased tendency by increasing age. We think that Korean perimenopausal women were exposed to osteoporosis and cardiovascular disease. Therefore as many as subsequent studies have established, hormone replacement therapy (HRT) will contribute to improving the quality of life for Korean perimenopausal women.
