TI  - UTILIZATION OF CLUSTERBEAN-MEAL IN RATIONS OF GROWING BUFFALO CALVES
T2  - INDIAN JOURNAL OF ANIMAL SCIENCES
LA  - English
AB  - A feeding trial extending for 366 days was conducted on 14 growing male Murrah buffalo calves, divided into 2 groups of 7 each. Group 1 (T1) was fed groundnut-cake (GNC) and wheat straw (WS), while the group 2(T2) was fed clusterbean-meal (CM) and WS in the ration of 50:50 on ME basis. Calves fed CM had significantly higher (P < 0.05) rate of body-weight gain (398.5 g/day) than calves fed GNC (306.8 d/day). Feed intake did not differ between treatments but DM intake/kg body-weight gain was significantly lower in group fed CM. Significantly higher (P < 0.01) digestibility of DM, CF and NFE, and efficiency of energy (ME) utilization were recorded in CM-fed group than in GNC-fed group. The differences observed between the groups in total plasma protein, non-protein- N, TVFAs and serum calcium were nonsignificant. The blood glucose level was significantly higher (P < 0.01) in CM-fed calves, while blood urea-N, serum cholesterol and plasma phosphorus were significantly lower. It was concluded that clusterbean-meal could safely be used in rations of growing buffalo calves to the extent of 50% of complete feed without any adverse effect on growth and energy utilization.
