TI  - DARIERS-DISEASE WITH CHANGES IN THE BONES
T2  - INTERNATIONAL JOURNAL OF DERMATOLOGY
LA  - English
AB  - Case 1: A 66-year-old man presented with a 20-year history of eczematous lesions, that worsened during warm weather, affecting the thorax, axillae, back, neck, and scalp. Biopsy of a lesion showed focal acantholytic dyskeratosis with acanthosis, suprabasalar clefts, and focal parakeratosis, confirming the clinical impression of Darier's disease. Skeletal survey showed a 10-15 mm oval cystic lesion with a radiolucent center and a denser wall in the proximal right femur (Fig. 1), and a pea-sized cyst in the right parietal-occipital region of the skull, also with a radiolucent center and a dense peripheral halo (Fig. 2). Tomograms confirmed the cystic nature of both lesions. A focal 1-cm area of bony sclerosis resembling an osteoma was also present in the distal right femur (Fig. 3). Repeat x-ray examination 3 years later showed no change in any of these lesions. Serum calcium and phosphorus were normal. Treatment consisted of topical therapy and occasional oral antimicrobials for suspected soft tissue infections. He was never treated with vitamin A, etretinate, or isotretinoin.
   Case 2: A 50-year-old man presented with an itchy papular eruption of 33-years duration that affected mainly the trunk. The eruption never completely resolved, but worsened during the summer, especially with sweating. Histological examination of a skin biopsy specimen showed multiple areas of intraepidermal acantholytic dyskeratosis with corps ronds and suprabasalar clefts confirming the clinical diagnosis of Darier's disease. Fasting serum triglyceride concentration was 332 mg/dL with elevated very-low-density lipoprotein. He did not have any musculoskeltal symptoms, but radiologic studies showed sclerotic changes in the right sacroiliac joint. The pattern was different from that seen in ankylosing spondylitis and he was negative for HLA-B27. Because of the elevated serum triglyceride level, he was never treated with vitamin A, etretinate, or isotretinoin.
