AB  - We investigated the influence of both the standard diet (20% of animal protein) and the low protein diets (LPD), including 10% Ketosteril (Fresenius Kabi, Germany) or 10% soy been protein SUPRO 760 on laboratory findings and the extent of the left ventricular hypertrophy (LVH) in Wistar rats with chronic renal failure (CRF). CRF was induced by 5/6 nephrectomy (NE). The control group (sham operated) was given the standard diet. In comparison to data obtained from the control group, data in the rats after NE given the standard diet showed the increased blood levels of urea, phosphorus and total cholesterol, as well as the decreased levels of total calcium. Furthermore, NE rats developed LVH. In the animals given either Ketosteril (R) or SUPRO 760 hypocalcemia and hypercholesterolemia were not developed. The levels of serum urea and phosphorus as well as LVH-index were much lower than those in the rats after NE and were given the standard diet (lower level of urea was on Ketosteril (R)). Thus, low-protein diets which include either Ketosteril (R) or SUPRO 760 delay the progression of experimental CRF in rats and decreases LVH. This study confirms the expediency of the use of Ketosteril (R) in the diet of renal patients. This study confirms the expediency of the use of Ketosteril (R) in the diet of renal patients.
