AB  - One group of rats were given whole milk alone and in other groups, the milk diet was supplemented by different doses of Mg salt solutions. The supplemented groups showed better rate of growth. Hypercalcemia, hypercholesteremia and hypomagnesemia were recorded in the serum of the rats receiving whole milk alone. The composition of the serum in the supplemented groups showed an opposite trend. The supplementation of magnesium salts seems to have reducing power in the serum cholesterol in experimental hypercholesteremia.
