TI  - EARLY ULTRASTRUCTURAL-CHANGES OF AORTA IN RATS LOADED WITH VITAMINE-D2 AND CHOLESTEROL
T2  - JAPANESE JOURNAL OF VETERINARY SCIENCE
LA  - English
AB  - Ultrastructural events in the early stage of the changes of the abdominal aorta in rats loaded with vitamin D2 and cholesterol were studied. The earliest appearing noticeable change was vesiculation in the intima which was attributable to the infiltration of plasma from the surface of endothelial cells. Then, intimal edema and deformation of the endothelial cells occurred. The subsequent course was characterized by degeneration of the inner and middle layers of the media accompanied with deposit of crystalline Ca salt. In the early stage of medial degeneration, crystallines of Ca salt first appeared within mitochondria of the smooth muscle cells. Apparently hypercalcemia due to vitamin D2 loading might play an important role in producing the early aortic lesions.
