AB  - Physiological hypercalcemia of the serum is reported in 7 laying hens. The levels of the filtrable Ca remained unchanged, but the non-filtrable adsorbable Ca increased 6-fold, and the non-filtrable, protein-bound Ca increased 5-fold. The total P as well as the P fractions remained within normal limits. In experimental hypercalcemia induced in 7 dogs by Ca gluconate, parathyroid extract, and also irradiated ergosterol, in the same animal, there was an increase in the total Ca with a maintenance of the normal relative proportions of the Ca fractions. There was an elevation in both fractions of P. No relationship existed between the levels of Cholesterol and the non-filtrable adsorbable Ca.
